history.text: Hi there!
Hi
Are you interested in Historical movies which deal with real life events
Yes, as long as they're done well.
Have you seen any movies like that lately?
Yes the Imitation Game, its really good and has a high rating 7.7/10
Oh cool. What real life events is it based on?

its based off Alan Turing who decryped german codes which help save thousands of lives in WW
II
Its known as one of the greatest movies of 2014
Oh wow. That was such an interesting time in history. All the research they were doing on codes, antibiotics etc. His story was so tragic, though.
Yes it was.. the romantic feelings he had for his friend and the unexpected ending of Alan was so sad
It's good to know the movie was well done, though. I might check it out.
Yeah! I mean it got 73/100 from Metacritic and a cinemaScore of A+!! isnt that impressive
Do you watch movies with high ratings?
I try to, but I more read Rotten Tomatoes. Is Metacritic an aggregator type service, too.
Yes it is. And not to mention Rotten Tomatoes gave this move a 91%. Looks like the aggregator you read gave this movie a high rating as well
Cool. I think I remember this won some Oscars?
Yes I believe so too. The performance of Benedict Cumberbatch as Alan Turing was phenomenal
Oh wow. I feel like from 2014-15 Cumberbatch was in everything. But he's such a versatile performer that it's always nice to see him.
Yes, even The Hollywood Reporter stated Cumberbatch was the highlight of the film with his charisma and his potraying of physical oddness was true talent
That's high praise from them, they can be vicious when they want to be.
Do you like period movies or more modern ones?
They sure can. But Empire stated is as a "superb thriller" and a classic which I can only agree with
Period is good but I enjoy more modern ones
Cool. I like  a variety of films, too.
The great thing about the ones set in the 20th century and later is that they're more relatable
At least for me.
Do ratings matter to you with movies?
For sure
have you watched any other movies with the actors - Keira Knightley, matthew goode or Tom Goodman-hill?
I like Keira Knightley a lot
Ratings matter to me, but I will also see something with poor ratings if I think it has potential
How about you?
Ratings matter to me alot
I also like Keira Knightley
How about Genre? Do you like Drama?
